        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 11:46AM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 1146 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mescalero, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mescalero, Lake Mescalero, Silver Lake, Bent, Elk Silver, Mountain
Park, Apache Summit, Upper Nogal Canyon, Fence Canyon, Portions of US
Highway 70 between Apache Summit and the Otero-Lincoln County Line,
Lower Nogal Canyon, Mescalero Apache School, Snow Canyon, Bear
Canyon, Soldier Canyon, and Laborcita Canyon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
